article.linkText: Tate puts up 25, Appalachian State defeats Marshall 65-58
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- — Myles Tate had 25 points in Appalachian State's 65-58 win over Marshall on Saturday night. Tate added six rebounds and five assists for the Mountaineers (24-5, 14-2 Sun Belt Conference). Donovan Gregory added 15 points and eight rebounds. Terence Harcum finished with 12 points. The Thundering Herd (12-17, 7-9) were led in scoring by Kevon Voyles and Kamdyn Curfman, both with 19 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
